      "content": "The term \"primitive\" is often an outdated and biased label, but historically, it was applied to groups lacking complex state apparatuses or industrial technology. These groups were often characterized by subsistence agriculture or nomadic lifestyles, and their social organization was typically based on small, tightly-knit kinship units rather than large, centralized governments. In a historical context, this description often referred to indigenous populations or societies in less industrialized regions.",
